But if you take any standard 3d convolution benchmark. Compile TF with MKL enabled and then check against w/o MKL, or better yet, look in VTune and see what's going on. You'll see that the 3d convolutions are not being forwarded to MKL. I've confirmed this with the Intel developers. (disclosure, I work for GE Research) Thanks, David

body:
Hi Ng,
We're working directly with the Intel Inferencing Engine development group
in Moscow.  We're under NDA with them so they're allowed to have the data.
But if you take any standard 3d convolution benchmark.  Compile TF with MKL
enabled and then check against w/o MKL, or better yet, look in VTune and
see what's going on.  You'll see that the 3d convolutions are not being
forwarded to MKL.  I've confirmed this with the Intel developers.
(disclosure, I work for GE Research)
Thanks,
David
